bad feeling about today.

244
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:19,875
And my hunches
are usually right.

245
00:12:19,958 --> 00:12:24,250
Even if I try to stop it,
something horrible will happen.

246
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:30,375
[FUCHI] Finally. You and
I are alone together.

247
00:12:36,916 --> 00:12:41,583
[MAMI] I don't want to die.
But I know I'm going to soon.

248
00:12:41,666 --> 00:12:46,833
I'll be dead. Nothing.
I'll completely cease to exist.

249
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:51,041
[MAMI cries]
I'm scared! I'm scared.

250
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:54,208
I can't take this!

251
00:12:54,291 --> 00:12:55,541
[MAMI gasps]

252
00:12:57,125 --> 00:13:00,041
Who's there? Who are you?

253
00:13:03,375 --> 00:13:05,833
[MAMI gasps]

254
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:12,000
[MAMI yells]

255
00:13:17,625 --> 00:13:20,083
[MAMI] Doctor! I don't
want to die here!

256
00:13:20,166 --> 00:13:22,000
I don't want to become dust!

257
00:13:22,083 --> 00:13:23,625
[KURODA] Mami, we're fighting
your disease

258
00:13:23,708 --> 00:13:27,166
to the best of our abilities,
I promise. But we need you to

259
00:13:27,250 --> 00:13:29,708
hold on to hope if you're
going to beat this.

260
00:13:29,791 --> 00:13:32,041
[MAMI]
Why bother? It's pointless!

261
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:33,958
I've seen the Grim Reaper!

262
00:13:34,041 --> 00:13:36,083
That is not the Grim Reaper.

263
00:13:36,166 --> 00:13:38,958
He's just a patient from
another ward in the hospital.

264
00:13:39,041 --> 00:13:42,208
You're lying! No human being
could look like that.

265
00:13:42,291 --> 00:13:43,958
I dream of him, too.

266
00:13:44,041 --> 00:13:47,583
He's some kind of creature
from the dark beyond!

267
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:49,500
[KURODA] A creature from
the dark beyond, huh?

268
00:13:49,583 --> 00:13:53,166
She's quite an intuitive girl,
I'll give her that much.

269
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:54,666
[DOCTOR A]
That intuition may be how

270
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:58,125
she realized she was ill.
And also why she fears death.

271
00:13:58,208 --> 00:14:00,583
A bit more than most patients,
it would seem.

272
00:14:00,666 --> 00:14:03,166
If our "Reaper" has started
wandering the hospital halls

273
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:05,291
at night, it's going to
turn into a real problem.

274
00:14:05,375 --> 00:14:08,083
He's likely doing it because
he's afraid to go to sleep.

275
00:14:08,166 --> 00:14:10,416
Actually, sir, could you tell
me a little more about this

276
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:11,708
special patient of yours?

277
00:14:11,791 --> 00:14:13,958
I imagine he'll be
waking up sometime soon.

278
00:14:14,041 --> 00:14:16,583
Why don't we go by
and pay him a visit?

279
00:14:16,666 --> 00:14:19,041
[DOCTOR A] I don't really know
much about his case at all.

280
00:14:19,125 --> 00:14:21,166
Mostly just hospital rumors.

281
00:14:21,250 --> 00:14:23,500
Could you fill me
in on his condition?

282
00:14:23,583 --> 00:14:25,250
I hear his dreams are unusual.

283
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:27,125
I suppose you haven't
been here long enough

284
00:14:27,208 --> 00:14:31,125
to hear the entire story.
Tetsurou Mukouda is his name.

285
00:14:31,208 --> 00:14:34,458
It was two months ago when he
first came to the hospital.

286
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:36,500
He complained he was suffering
from what he called

287
00:14:36,583 --> 00:14:38,208
"long dreams."

288
00:14:38,291 --> 00:14:39,916
Long dreams, huh?

289
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,041
Could you be a little
more specific, please?

290
00:14:42,125 --> 00:14:43,875
[TETSURO]
They're getting worse.

291
00:14:43,958 --> 00:14:45,125
I don't know when they started,

292
00:14:45,208 --> 00:14:47,458
but it was a month ago
when I first noticed.

293
00:14:47,541 --> 00:14:49,791
I would go to sleep normally,
and a single night's dream

294
00:14:49,875 --> 00:14:52,958
would feel like it lasted two,
maybe three full days.

295
00:14:53,041 --> 00:14:55,291
[KURODA]
Hm... So...

296
00:14:55,375 --> 00:14:58,916
What you mean is that they felt
lengthy after you'd woken up.

297
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,333
No, it's the dreams
themselves that feel long,

298
00:15:01,416 --> 00:15:03,083
like I'm living every
second of them.

299
00:15:03,166 --> 00:15:05,875
At first I thought I was just
imagining it, but with each day

300
00:15:05,958 --> 00:15:07,500
they became increasingly longer.

301
00:15:07,583 --> 00:15:09,500
Which might be fine if they
were all good dreams,

302
00:15:09,583 --> 00:15:11,375
but there are plenty
of nightmares, too,

303
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:14,000
so it's like being trapped
in hell sometimes.

304
00:15:14,083 --> 00:15:15,666
[KURODA]
Hm. And how long do your dreams

305
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:17,125
feel like they're lasting now?

306
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:20,000
[TETSURO] Well, Last night's
dream was one whole year.

307
00:15:20,083 --> 00:15:21,375
An entire year?

308
00:15:21,458 --> 00:15:23,375
[TETSURO]
Doctor. I'm serious.

309
00:15:23,458 --> 00:15:25,500
[TETSURO] It's getting harder
to tell when I'm dreaming

310
00:15:25,583 --> 00:15:26,708
and when I'm really awake,

311
00:15:26,791 --> 00:15:29,333
and it's starting to
ruin my everyday life.

312
00:15:29,416 --> 00:15:32,666
Think about it. For me,
yesterday was a year ago.

313
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:34,250
A year I lived.

314
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:37,500
[KURODA] I decided to admit him
and monitor his sleep cycles.

315
00:15:37,583 --> 00:15:39,041
It was fairly
standard procedure,

316
00:15:39,125 --> 00:15:43,416
all things considered.
And, then, on that first night.

317
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:44,958
[KURODA gasps]

318
00:15:49,916 --> 00:15:51,916
[KURODA] He experienced
full-body convulsions

319
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:54,083
and rapid eye movement.

320
00:15:54,166 --> 00:15:57,125
But those both ended as
quickly as they had begun.

321
00:15:57,208 --> 00:15:59,958
His brain activity indicated
he was in the deepest phase

322
00:16:00,041 --> 00:16:02,208
of the sleep cycle
at that moment.

323
00:16:02,291 --> 00:16:04,333
[KURODA]
Hey! Listen to me. Wake up!

324
00:16:04,416 --> 00:16:06,333
[TETSURO grunts]

325
00:16:07,708 --> 00:16:10,208
Tell me, were you
dreaming just now?

326
00:16:11,791 --> 00:16:13,958
[TETSURO grunts]
Wait, where am I?

327
00:16:14,041 --> 00:16:16,375
You're in the hospital,
you admitted yourself yesterday,

328
00:16:16,458 --> 00:16:18,666
do you have any
memory of that at all?

329
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:21,583
[TETSURO grunts]
Wait, what?

330
00:16:21,666 --> 00:16:23,916
Oh. I remember now.

331
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:28,833
That's right, I talked to you in
your office. I was dreaming.

332
00:16:28,916 --> 00:16:34,083
It was a nightmare. And it
lasted for a year and a half.

333
00:16:34,166 --> 00:16:35,958
[KURODA] My instincts
told me that this man

334
00:16:36,041 --> 00:16:40,000
was not lying to me.
I believed that he truly was

335
00:16:40,083 --> 00:16:42,791
suffering from
these long dreams.

336
00:16:44,291 --> 00:16:46,333
[TETSURO]
Doctor. When will I be cured?

337
00:16:46,416 --> 00:16:47,958
I want my life back.

338
00:16:48,041 --> 00:16:50,125
I have a few potential
treatments in mind,

339
00:16:50,208 --> 00:16:51,916
but I need you
to be patient.

340
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,916
The dream I had last night
went on for ten years.

341
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,666
They just keep getting longer.

342
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:00,250
They're only illusions.
Your actual dreams

343
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:02,916
are no more than a few
moments long at the most.

344
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,791
There's no reason for you
to be afraid of them.

345
00:17:05,875 --> 00:17:08,083
[TETSURO] No offense, but you're
only saying that because

346
00:17:08,166 --> 00:17:11,250
you've never had a dream
like mine, Doctor.

347
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:14,416
You don't know how
realistic they feel to me.

348
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:17,333
How disturbing and
terribly lonely they are.

349
00:17:17,416 --> 00:17:19,666
How frightening they can be.

350
00:17:19,750 --> 00:17:22,500
Yes, but you must understand
it's all in your mind.

351
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:25,333
In the meantime, we're working
diligently to find the cause

352
00:17:25,416 --> 00:17:26,416
of these dreams.

353
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,000
[TETSURO]
Please, you have to hurry.

354
00:17:28,083 --> 00:17:30,541
Otherwise, I'm concerned that
my dreams will eventually last

355
00:17:30,625 --> 00:17:33,541
a hundred years,
maybe even more than that.

356
00:17:33,625 --> 00:17:37,250
If that does happen,
I think I'll lose my mind.

357
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:39,625
[KURODA] And, just as
he predicted, the length

358
00:17:39,708 --> 00:17:43,333
of his dreams seemed to increase
exponentially over time.

359
00:17:43,416 --> 00:17:46,541
Eventually this became
obvious to his doctors.

360
00:17:46,625 --> 00:17:48,958
It was like we were watching
some kind of evolution

361
00:17:49,041 --> 00:17:51,375
of the mind unfold before us.

362
00:17:54,291 --> 00:17:56,833
Good morning, Tetsuro,
are you awake?

363
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:03,625
What am I doing in this place?
And who are you people?

364
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:07,416
I'm Dr. Kuroda, your physician.
Try to remember.

365
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,208
[TETSURO groans]

366
00:18:09,291 --> 00:18:10,791
No!

367
00:18:10,875 --> 00:18:13,666
Lately, he's started having
bizarre reactions and delusions

368
00:18:13,750 --> 00:18:15,166
when he first wakes up.

369
00:18:15,250 --> 00:18:17,125
[DOCTOR A] Do you suppose
he thinks he's still dreaming,

370
00:18:17,208 --> 00:18:18,875
living some other life?

371
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:22,833
Where did my Mami go?
Why isn't my wife Mami here?

372
00:18:22,916 --> 00:18:24,583
That's right, this is
the hospital where

373
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:27,458
I first met her,
isn't it? Where?

374
00:18:27,541 --> 00:18:29,291
Where's my precious Mami?

375
00:18:29,375 --> 00:18:31,791
[NURSE] Mami. You have
to eat something.

376
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:36,083
[MAMI] I don't feel like it.
The idea of dying is so--

377
00:18:36,166 --> 00:18:38,083
[TETSURO gasps]
Mami!

378
00:18:38,166 --> 00:18:40,083
No!

379
00:18:40,166 --> 00:18:42,166
Mami!

380
00:18:43,333 --> 00:18:45,958
I knew the Grim Reaper
would come for me again!

381
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:48,208
That's enough, you need
to go back to your room.

382
00:18:48,291 --> 00:18:51,208
The Reaper? That's what
she called me.

383
00:18:51,291 --> 00:18:54,875
I remember now.
It was all a dream.

384
00:18:54,958 --> 00:18:58,083
[TETSURO] Doctor, I'm scared.
How is this going to end?

385
00:18:58,166 --> 00:19:01,291
If my dreams continue to get
longer, then what happens?

386
00:19:01,375 --> 00:19:04,750
What if they become infinite
nightmares I can't wake from.

387
00:19:04,833 --> 00:19:06,958
If I start dreaming
endless dreams,

388
00:19:07,041 --> 00:19:12,958
then what will become of me?
Will I disappear completely?

389
00:19:14,125 --> 00:19:16,583
[yells] I'm so scared!

390
00:19:16,666 --> 00:19:19,666
I don't want to die, please,
someone fix me.

391
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:23,250
[NURSE]
It's okay! Calm down.

392
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:26,125
[KURODA] It's unfortunate.
I've never seen a patient

393
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:29,250
who has such an intense
fear of death before.

394
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:31,625
And what about
Tetsurou Mukouda?

395
00:19:31,708 --> 00:19:34,458
I can't imagine how far into
the future he's dreamed now,

396
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:37,708
or if he's capable of
coming back to reality.

397
00:20:08,291 --> 00:20:09,583
[KURODA gasps]

398
00:20:27,583 --> 00:20:30,833
[KURODA] As I watched the husk
of his remains blow away,

399
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:35,083
I wondered if his mind had
vanished into an unending dream.

400
00:20:38,125 --> 00:20:40,416
[KURODA] Later, I discovered
an unidentified,

401
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:44,333
crystallized material within
what was left of his brain.

402
00:20:44,416 --> 00:20:47,833
I suspected it had something
to do with his unusual dreams.

403
00:20:47,916 --> 00:20:50,000
It was the only explanation
I could think of,

404
00:20:50,083 --> 00:20:51,916
but I had no proof.

405
00:20:54,583 --> 00:20:56,875
[KURODA] How are you
feeling today, Mami?

406
00:20:56,958 --> 00:20:59,416
[MAMI grunts]
Dr. Kuroda.

407
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:02,458
I'm feeling
pretty good, actually.

408
00:21:02,541 --> 00:21:04,583
Wonderful.

409
00:21:04,666 --> 00:21:09,000
It's strange, though, Doctor.
There is one odd thing.

410
00:21:09,083 --> 00:21:12,583
Lately, it seems like
I dream for so long.

411
00:21:12,666 --> 00:21:15,250
[KURODA softly gasps]

412
00:21:17,125 --> 00:21:19,333
[DOCTOR A] Sir. Have you
noticed the differences

413
00:21:19,416 --> 00:21:21,541
in Mami Takeshima's condition?

414
00:21:21,625 --> 00:21:24,500
Her appearance is starting
to change, too, drastically.

415
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:26,791
She's looking like he did.

416
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:28,416
What do you think
is to blame?

417
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,666
[KURODA] I've been administering
the crystals I retrieved from

418
00:21:30,750 --> 00:21:32,833
Testurou Mukouda's
brain to her.

419
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:34,708
They appear to be
affecting her similarly.

420
00:21:34,791 --> 00:21:36,166
[gasps]
Wait, you did what?

421
00:21:36,250 --> 00:21:38,375
[KURODA] Her fear of dying
and the end of her existence

422
00:21:38,458 --> 00:21:41,500
in this world consumed her.
Even if I knew another approach,

423
00:21:41,583 --> 00:21:43,750
that mindset would
negate any treatment.

424
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:46,416
But what if she could dream
an eternal dream instead?

425
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:48,083
It would amount to her
life never ending,

426
00:21:48,166 --> 00:21:49,583
at least not in her mind.

427
00:21:49,666 --> 00:21:52,666
Even if, in reality, it was
all just an illusion.

428
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:54,250
[gasps]

429
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:56,625
[KURODA] If humanity actually
had the means to lose themselves

430
00:21:56,708 --> 00:21:57,958
in endless dreams,

431
00:21:58,041 --> 00:22:00,625
think of what that would
mean for us as a species.

432
00:22:00,708 --> 00:22:02,875
We would be able to
permanently rid ourselves

433
00:22:02,958 --> 00:22:04,500
of the fear of death.

434
00:22:04,583 --> 00:22:06,875
Just as Mami has.

